    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>
                <date>March 16, '54</date>
            </p>
            <p>Reverend Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">We address you upon a<lb/> subject, the selection of a minister
                for<lb/> the German Congregation of <placeName>San Francisco</placeName><lb/> upon
                which, we desire to elicit your<lb/> assistance as the superior advantages<lb/>
                acquired by your position places you<lb/> within reach of all the attendant facts
                of<lb/> any importance.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">We send you an advertise-<lb/>ment for insertion &amp; take the
                Liberty<lb/> of referring <add>to</add> you which you can omit<lb/> in the columns
                of your Occident if you<lb/> deem we have no right to intrude upon<lb/> your privacy
                &amp; claim your assistance in<lb/> our causeâ€”</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Its tone <del>much</del> will inform you<lb/> generally of our want
                but particularly<lb/> bear in mind we are a young, an honest<lb/> energetic, frank
                    <add>congregation</add> &amp; <add>we</add>
                <del>I</del> might add somewhat<lb/> tinctured of the moderate reforms of the
                age<lb/> &amp; desire to select a minister compatible<lb/> with these views. With
                these ideas we<lb/> offered the <persName>Revd J K Gutheim</persName> this
                position<lb/> but circumstances well known to you<lb/> prevented his acceptance. He
                would<lb/> be a true model of what we desire to obtain</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>We write these facts &amp; others as a committee<lb/> appointed for that purpose to
                correspond<lb/> with you &amp; you may use such as in<lb/> your judgment, you deem
                proper for an<lb/> Editorial notice on the subject.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">We are far removed from the seat<lb/> of similar applications with a
                lazy &amp; uncertain communication between us &amp;<lb/> necessarily must leave the
                matter in<lb/> the hands of some one who like yourself<lb/> well understands our
                want &amp; can refer<lb/> us some excellent personâ€”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">We do not want an old man if<lb/> we can avoid it, for we conceive
                that<lb/> there will not be the Harmony existing as<lb/> between congregation &amp;
                a young minister<lb/> of about 35 years of age, whose youth will<lb/> blend him to
                the errors of his young flock.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Should the minister please us<lb/> he will undoubtedly be elected
                for life<lb/> as soon as his first term expires, we<lb/> want an English Scholar by
                all<lb/> means, but one conversant with German<lb/> also will suit us betterâ€”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The people here are very liberal<lb/> &amp; have contributed in a
                fortnight about<lb/> $20,000 to erect a brick synagogue on</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>a lot in one of our principal <sic>street</sic><lb/> in size 65 ft x 137<hi
                    rend="underline">6</hi> feet.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">We have about two Hundred families<lb/> one half of whom belong to
                our synagogue<lb/> &amp; many <hi rend="underline">promising</hi> young men who
                will<lb/> do much to increase the community.<lb/> There are about 50 children &amp;
                a number<lb/> of them who would attend school in the<lb/> basement of the proposed
                synagogueâ€”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Our attendants are many at divine<lb/> service, considering our
                officiating Hazon<lb/> &amp; we never have less than 25 or 30 present.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The building is to be a handsome<lb/> Gothic brick structure &amp;
                to be paid for<lb/> fully out of our funds so that we may<lb/> have it
                unencumberedâ€”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">We have again of members to our<lb/> synagogue of about 33 per cent
                in the<lb/> last six months &amp; now number about<lb/> 100 contributing
                members.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">A minister would be necessarily<lb/> exposed to heavy expenses &amp;
                could not<lb/> possibly subsist upon less than $40<lb/> a week, were he to supply
                himself<lb/> amply with necessaries. Of course<lb/> he could curtail these expenses
                but<lb/> it would not suit the people to have<lb/> a penurious minister.</p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p>The perquisites are $10 for a marriage of<lb/> which he might reckon upon <hi
                    rend="underline">2</hi> a month<lb/> at least. For school children &amp;c
                in<lb/> proportion &amp; when teaching the Parassah &amp;c.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Will you please inform us very<lb/> privately concerning the
                applicants as<lb/> to their abilities, qualifications characters<lb/> &amp; should
                you wish your name kept<lb/> secret in the correspondence we shall<lb/> do so. Let
                us hear from you if you<lb/> desire any further information in the<lb/> subject
                &amp; we will forthwith furnish it.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">We will pay the expenses here<lb/> of any minister recommended by
                you<lb/> as fully competent &amp; extremely praise<lb/> worthy, in case he should be
                elected<lb/> to the probationary term by the congregation</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">We have the Honor to be</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Yrs <sic>Every</sic> Respy.</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author"><add>?</add> Emanuel</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <persName><add>?</add> Labatt</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <persName>Ann</persName>
            </p>
            <p>To the Reverend</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
